The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Sarda plea

 OUR LEGAL REPORTER

 Calcutta, April 9: A division bench of the Supreme Court today admitted a special leave petition by Amit Sarda, an accused in the fake blood test kit case, challenging a Calcutta High Court order refusing him anticipatory bail.

 The apex court directed the petitioner to serve notices to the respondents of the case and adjourned the matter till next week. It asked police not to arrest Amit, the son of main accused Govind Sarda, in the intervening period. 




